{{see|και}}
==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*Apparently a primary particle, having a copulative and sometimes also a cumulative force

===Pronunciation===
*καί / kai / kahee

===Particle===
'''καί'''

# and, also, even, so, then, too, etc.; often used in connection (or composition) with other particles or small words: - and, also, both, but, even, for, if, indeed, likewise, moreover, or, so, that, then, therefore, when, yea, yet.

